# EMC React Component Patterns

## React Spectrum â€” S2 first, v3 fallback

**Prefer** `@react-spectrum/s2` for new and refactored UI. Use `@adobe/react-spectrum` (v3) only when there is no suitable S2 component or you must align with an existing v3-only boundary.

```tsx
// Preferred â€” Spectrum 2
import { Button, TextField } from '@react-spectrum/s2'
import { style } from '@react-spectrum/s2/style' with { type: 'macro' }
import Edit from '@react-spectrum/s2/icons/Edit'

// Fallback â€” v3 (when S2 has no equivalent)
import { Button, TextField, Flex, View } from '@adobe/react-spectrum'
import Edit from '@spectrum-icons/workflow/Edit'
```

### Spectrum interaction and layout (both stacks)
- Use `onPress` on Spectrum buttons/links (not `onClick`) unless working with plain DOM
- **S2:** layout and spacing via `style()` macro and S2 docs; **v3:** `Flex`, `Grid`, `View` with dimension props (`size-*`, `static-size-*`) and token spacing
- Minimize `UNSAFE_style` / `UNSAFE_className`; comment when required
- **v3 surfaces:** `defaultTheme`, `Provider`, `colorScheme`, `scale` in App as today
- **v3 collections:** `<Picker>`, `<ComboBox>`, `<ListView>` use `<Item key={}>` children

See `react-spectrum-s2.mdc` and `react-spectrum-v3.mdc` for stack-specific detail.

## Component Patterns

### Functional Components Only
```tsx
// Standard pattern â€” React.FC with typed props
interface MyComponentProps {
  ims: IMS
  data?: SomeType
}

const MyComponent: React.FC<MyComponentProps> = ({ ims, data }) => {
  // hooks at top
  const { apiService } = useApi()
  const { showToast } = useToast()
  
  return <View>...</View>
}

export default MyComponent
```

### Context Usage
```tsx
// Access API service
const { apiService } = useApi()

// Show toast notifications
const { showToast } = useToast()
showToast('Event saved', 'success')

// Access event form state (inside EventFormProvider)
const { formData, updateFormData } = useEventFormComponent({ componentId: 'myComponent' })
```

### Custom Hooks

| Hook                       | Purpose                                    | Location         |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ | ---------------- |
| `useLoadData(loadFn)`      | Data fetching with loading/error/reload    | `hooks/`         |
| `useEventFormComponent()`  | EventForm lifecycle registration           | `hooks/`         |
| `useEventFormData()`       | Simplified form data access (read/write)   | `hooks/`         |
| `useEventFormSave()`       | Save/publish logic for event form          | `hooks/`         |
| `useSeriesFormComponent()` | SeriesForm lifecycle registration          | `hooks/`         |
| `useDevToken()`            | Dev token state management                 | `hooks/`         |
| `useEventTypeFeatures()`   | Feature flags per event type               | `hooks/`         |
| `useRsvpConfig()`          | RSVP form configuration                    | `hooks/`         |
| `useSafeState()`           | State updates safe after unmount           | `hooks/`         |

### Data Loading Pattern
```tsx
const { data, loading, error, reload } = useLoadData(async () => {
  return await apiService.getEventsList(seriesId)
})

if (loading) return <LoadingSpinner message="Loading events..." />
if (error) return <Text>Error: {error.message}</Text>
```

## Shared Components

### DataTable
```tsx
<DataTable
  items={events}
  columns={[
    { key: 'title', name: 'Title', sortable: true },
    { key: 'status', name: 'Status', render: (item) => <StatusBadge status={item.status} /> },
  ]}
  actions={[
    { type: 'edit', onAction: (item) => navigate(`/events/edit/${item.eventId}`) },
    { type: 'delete', onAction: (item) => handleDelete(item) },
  ]}
  pageSize={10}
  isLoading={loading}
/>
```

### FormWizard
```tsx
<FormWizard
  steps={steps}
  currentStep={currentStep}
  onStepChange={setCurrentStep}
  onSave={handleSave}
  onPublish={handlePublish}
  isSaving={isSaving}
  renderSideNav={() => <StepNavigation />}
/>
```

### ResourceDashboardLayout
```tsx
<ResourceDashboardLayout
  title="Events"
  searchPlaceholder="Search events..."
  onSearch={handleSearch}
  actions={<Button onPress={handleCreate}>Create Event</Button>}
>
  <DataTable ... />
</ResourceDashboardLayout>
```

## Dialog Pattern
```tsx
// Controlled dialog with Spectrum DialogTrigger
<DialogTrigger isOpen={isOpen} onOpenChange={(open) => !open && onClose()}>
  <div style={{ display: 'none' }} />  {/* Hidden trigger element */}
  <Dialog size="M">
    <Heading>Dialog Title</Heading>
    <Divider />
    <Content>
      {/* Dialog content */}
    </Content>
    <ButtonGroup>
      <Button variant="secondary" onPress={onClose}>Cancel</Button>
      <Button variant="accent" onPress={onConfirm}>Confirm</Button>
    </ButtonGroup>
  </Dialog>
</DialogTrigger>
```

## Type Definitions

All domain types live in `web-src/src/types/`:
- `domain.ts` â€” EventFormData, SeriesApiResponse, Venue, ProfileData, SponsorData, etc.
- `runtime.ts` â€” IMS, Runtime, IMSProfile (Adobe ExC Shell types)
- `attendee.ts` â€” Attendee-specific types
- Types are re-exported through `types/index.ts`

When creating new types, add them to the appropriate file in `types/` and export from `index.ts`.

## Code Style

- No semicolons (project convention)
- Prefer `const` arrow functions for components
- Barrel exports (`index.ts`) in every directory
- Import order: React â†’ third-party â†’ local (contexts â†’ hooks â†’ services â†’ types â†’ utils)
